and out of phase and so

00:22:35.580 --> 00:22:36.900
forth in the wave functions.

00:22:36.900 --> 00:22:38.850
And then you square
it to find out

00:22:38.850 --> 00:22:40.620
the probability distributions.

00:22:40.620 --> 00:22:42.780
But now, when I go
to a crystal, you

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:45.090
see you're taking this
to the next level,

00:22:45.090 --> 00:22:47.750
to the next infinite level.

00:22:47.750 --> 00:22:50.090
So now, you don't just
have another atom there,

00:22:50.090 --> 00:22:53.100
you've got an atom everywhere,
all the way out to infinity.

00:22:53.100 --> 00:22:57.300
And what ends up happening
is that, as we'll see,

00:22:57.300 --> 00:23:01.280
