But that's, again, not--

00:53:01.670 --> 00:53:03.590
we don't need to know that.

00:53:03.590 --> 00:53:05.270
What we need to know is this.

00:53:05.270 --> 00:53:07.160
This is what we need to know.

00:53:07.160 --> 00:53:09.300
This is the punchline of it all.

00:53:09.300 --> 00:53:12.860
So we've gone through
some derivation.

00:53:12.860 --> 00:53:15.005
We won't do more
much more derivation.

00:53:15.005 --> 00:53:16.130
But this is the punch line.

00:53:16.130 --> 00:53:17.838
This is what you got
to take out of this,

00:53:17.838 --> 00:53:20.900
so please do take this away.

00:53:20.900 --> 00:53:25.310
When we had hydrogen atoms,
when we solved the Schrodinger

00:53:25.310 --> 00:53:29.030
equation for a
hydrogen atom, we saw

00:53:29.030 --> 00:53:32.550
that the way we did it was we
imposed spherical symmetry.

00:53:32.550 --> 00:53:34.070
So we had a symmetry.

00:53:34.070 --> 00:53:35.570
We did have a symmetry.

00:53:35.570 --> 00:53:39.200
It wasn't a crystal
symmetry, which I showed you,

00:53:39.200 --> 00:53:40.340
14 Bravais lattices.

00:53:40.340 --> 00:53:42.200
But it was a
symmetry, spherical.

00:53:42.200 --> 00:53:46.550
And when I imposed that, we saw
that there are-- these quantum

00:53:46.550 --> 00:53:48.650
numbers came out, remember?

00:53:48.650 --> 00:53:49.350
We did that.

00:53:49.350 --> 00:53:50.930
And that was so
cool, because it just

00:53:50.930 --> 00:53:54.140
solved so many of the
issues of the time,

00:53:54.140 --> 00:53:56.780
just the fact that
electrons were quantized

00:53:56.780 --> 00:53:58.400
was so important.

00:53:58.400 --> 00:53:59.180
All right.

00:53:59.180 --> 00:54:03.070
Now, we have a new
kind of symmetry.

00:54:03.070 --> 00:54:05.185
We have something called
translational symmetry.

00:54:05.185 --> 00:54:07.060
We're still solving the
Schrodinger equation,

00:54:07.060 --> 00:54:08.590
but now it's a periodic solid.

00:54:08.590 --> 00:54:11.320
And when this kind of
symmetry is in the game,

00:54:11.320 --> 00:54:15.680
we have a different
kind of quantum number.

00:54:15.680 --> 00:54:16.970
That's what matters most here.

00:54:16.970 --> 00:54:18.800
We have a different
kind of quantum number.

00:54:18.800 --> 00:54:25.340
We have a quantum number that
is a reciprocal lattice vector.

00:54:25.340 --> 00:54:28.850
It's a vector in
reciprocal space.

00:54:28.850 --> 00:54:31.560
That's the key.

00:54:31.560 --> 00:54:33.260
And because we
have-- you see, just

00:54:33.260 --> 00:54:37.100
like-- so these l's and
m's had their rules.

00:54:37.100 --> 00:54:39.860
This could be plus or minus
that and so forth and so on.

00:54:39.860 --> 00:54:41.210
And so you could--

00:54:41.210 --> 00:54:44.960
they lived within I don't know.

00:54:44.960 --> 00:54:47.180
They lived within
in the counting

00:54:47.180 --> 00:54:50.610
of the principal quantum number.

00:54:50.610 --> 00:54:52.150
Now, we have a
different situation.

00:54:52.150 --> 00:54:55.260
We have a quantum
number that can vary.

00:54:55.260 --> 00:54:57.330
It doesn't have to just be 0, 1.

00:54:57.330 --> 00:55:00.750
Or it's not necessarily tied to
the principle quantum number.

00:55:00.750 --> 00:55:02.040
But it can vary.

00:55:02.040 --> 00:55:07.170
And its domain of varying
is that Brillouin zone.

00:55:07.170 --> 00:55:07.830
That's it.

00:55:07.830 --> 00:55:09.900
So that's where it can play.

00:55:09.900 --> 00:55:14.717
These guys have
variations dictated

00:55:14.717 --> 00:55:16.050
by the principal quantum number.

00:55:16.050 --> 00:55:19.660
This has variations dictated
by the Brillouin zone.

00:55:19.660 --> 00:55:23.480
That's really the key
here, the Brillouin zone,

00:55:23.480 --> 00:55:26.805
which comes about
from reciprocal space.

00:55:26.805 --> 00:55:27.680
Is everybody with me?

00:55:34.840 --> 00:55:37.500
Well, here's just a drawing.

00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:38.740
I don't even know where--

00:55:38.740 --> 00:55:40.840
I should really have
a reference here.

00:55:40.840 --> 00:55:44.428
This is one of my
Google image searches.

00:55:44.428 --> 00:55:45.220
And there are many.

00:55:45.220 --> 00:55:47.140
And you can look
at drawings online.

00:55:47.140 --> 00:55:51.970
But if you have a very
simple wave function--

00:55:51.970 --> 00:55:53.680
that's the real and
imaginary parts--

00:55:53.680 --> 00:55:56.800
and you have some periodically
repeating function--

00:55:56.800 --> 00:56:00.160
so that's my psi, and that's
my periodic function--

00:56:00.160 --> 00:56:02.830
then you can get a
sense of this variation

00:56:02.830 --> 00:56:04.750
that I'm talking about.

00:56:04.750 --> 00:56:08.390
This is a very simple
one-dimensional example.

00:56:08.390 --> 00:56:11.120
So I have a one-dimensional
wave function.

00:56:11.120 --> 00:56:13.830
And I have a periodically
repeating function.

00:56:13.830 --> 00:56:15.830
And remember, what
Bloch's Theorem says

00:56:15.830 --> 00:56:18.350
is that that is
now how I'm going

00:56:18.350 --> 00:56:20.480
to write a solution to
the Schrodinger equation.

00:56:20.480 --> 00:56:26.210
It's going to be a combination
of a plane wave like that,

00:56:26.210 --> 00:56:28.440
where k is in the
reciprocal space,

00:56:28.440 --> 00:56:30.440
and some periodically
repeating function.

00:56:30.440 --> 00:56:36.110
And just to illustrate that you
can get variation now, check

00:56:36.110 --> 00:56:40.310
out what happens when I change
k from, say, something not

00:56:40.310 --> 00:56:43.560
equal to 0 to something
like pi over a,

00:56:43.560 --> 00:56:46.850
you can see that these
functions change dramatically.

00:56:46.850 --> 00:56:52.010
The wave function of
the crystal changes.

00:56:52.010 --> 00:56:52.850
Everybody see that?

00:56:55.820 --> 00:56:57.893
So that's really important.

00:56:57.893 --> 00:56:59.810
And the reason that's
important and the reason

00:56:59.810 --> 00:57:03.050
this is all going to come
home for us as we move on

00:57:03.050 --> 00:57:09.800
to seeing why this all matters
is that that means you have

00:57:09.800 --> 00:57:16.380
energies that also depend on k.

00:57:16.380 --> 00:57:22.580
The energies also depend on this
variation in reciprocal space.

00:57:22.580 --> 00:57:23.420
All right.

00:57:23.420 --> 00:57:25.230
So now, if I'm in
reciprocal space,

00:57:25.230 --> 00:57:27.380
and I move from the
origin out to the edge

00:57:27.380 --> 00:57:30.410
of the Brillouin zone, not
only am I changing my function,

00:57:30.410 --> 00:57:32.210
I'm changing this.

00:57:32.210 --> 00:57:38.360
I'm changing-- the position
of this level can vary now.

00:57:38.360 --> 00:57:39.260
It now can vary.

00:57:39.260 --> 00:57:42.770
It can move up or down.

00:57:42.770 --> 00:57:49.535
And that's the key
result, the one that's

00:57:49.535 --> 00:57:50.660
going to matter most to us.

00:57:57.070 --> 00:58:00.870
Is everybody-- any questions?

00:58:00.870 --> 00:58:01.563
This is-- yeah?

